hopobject.body: I love this site healthcapital.ch The three funds managed by the Manarin investment advisoryfirm were eligible to own lower-cost "institutional" shares inthe mutual funds, but instead, owned more costly "class A"shares, typically intended for retail investors. As a result,they racked up ongoing 12b-1 fees, or charges for mutual fundmarketing expenses. The firm refunded the fees to the LifetimeAchievement Fund but not the $685,000 incurred by the other twofunds.
